Assignment Operators

LogTScript supports multiple assignment operators with different width-handling behaviors.

---

"="

Strict assignment.

The assigned value must have exactly the same width as the destination.

No padding is performed.

Syntax

wire = value

Examples

3wire q = 001

Result:

001

---

3wire q = 1

Error:

Expected 3 bits, got 1 bit.

---

8wire q = 10101010

Result:

10101010

---

":="

Left-pad assignment.

If the assigned value is shorter than the destination width, zeros are added on the left.

Syntax

wire := value

Examples

3wire q := 1

Result:

001

---

3wire q := 10

Result:

010

---

8wire q := 101

Result:

00000101

---

8wire q := 11110000

Result:

11110000

---

"=:"

Right-pad assignment.

If the assigned value is shorter than the destination width, zeros are added on the right.

Syntax

wire =: value

Examples

3wire q =: 1

Result:

100

---

3wire q =: 10

Result:

100

---

8wire q =: 101

Result:

10100000

---

8wire q =: 11110000

Result:

11110000

---

Example with ASM

32wire prog =:
.myisa {
  LOAD \0
  ADDI \3
  SUBI \2
  STORE \1
}

The generated bitstream is stored starting from the most significant side and padded with zeros on the right if needed.

---

":"

Initial assignment.

Assigns the initial value of a wire.

Syntax

wire : value

Examples

3wire q : 1

---

8wire counter : 00000000

---

1wire state : 0

---

Summary

Operator| Behavior
"=" Strict assignment
":=" Left-pad assignment
"=:" Right-pad assignment
":" Initial assignment
